<title>USA: Nucor and CSN consider Brzailian mini-mill.</title>
<headline>Nucor and CSN consider Brzailian mini-mill.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Companhia Siderurgica Nacional SA a Brazilian company, and Nucor Corp said they have signed a letter of intent to determine the feasibility of jointly building and running a steel plant in the state of Ceara, Brazil.</p>
<p>The new project, said the companies, would be the first mini-mill to be installed in Brzail.</p>
<p>Companhia Siderurgica Nacional is the largest integrated steel producer in Latin America.  Nucor is one of the largest steel producers in North America.  Late Thursday morning its shares were trading at 55-1/8, up 1.</p>
